The HRMS service layer has been created. Here's the summary:

File Created: app/services/hrms_store.py
The file contains all 8 required functions:

list_leave_types(db) - Returns all leave types from hr_leave_types_demo
create_leave_type(db, name, max_days, created_by) - Creates a new leave type
list_leave_requests(db, resource_id=None, is_approved=None) - Lists leave requests with join to leave types, supports filtering by resource and status (PENDING/APPROVED/REJECTED)
create_leave_request(db, resource_id, leave_type_id, from_date, to_date, reason) - Creates a new leave request with auto-calculated NumDays
approve_leave_request(db, request_id, approver_id, decision, remarks="") - Approves/rejects a leave request
compute_leave_balance(db, resource_id) - Computes leave balance across all leave types for a resource
list_payslips(db, resource_id=None, pay_month=None) - Lists payslips with optional filters
create_payslip(db, resource_id, pay_month, basic, allowances, deductions, created_by) - Creates a new payslip with auto-calculated NetPay
Also Updated: app/models/db_schema.py
Added the three HRMS model classes:

HrLeaveType - Maps to hr_leave_types_demo
HrLeaveRequest - Maps to hr_leave_requests_demo
HrPayslip - Maps to hr_payslips_demo
